// godfall/packs/talents.db
{"_id":"t001","name":"Attribute Increase","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/upgrade.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Increase one attribute score by 1. An attribute cannot be increased above 18 with this talent.\n(This talent can be taken multiple times.)</p>"}}
{"_id":"t002","name":"Resilient","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/strong.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You gain additional Hit Points equal to your level.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t003","name":"Weapon Skill","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/sword.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Choose a weapon type you are not skilled with (e.g., Bows, Maces, Spears, Shields).\nYou become skilled with it and gain it as a Weapon Skill with a +0 bonus.\n(This talent can be taken multiple times.)</p>"}}
{"_id":"t004","name":"Armor Training","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/armor.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You become skilled with a type of armor you are not already skilled with (Light, Medium, or Heavy).</p>"}}
{"_id":"t005","name":"Alert","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/eye.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You gain a +2 bonus to your Initiative rolls.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t006","name":"Expert Dodger","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/parry.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You gain a +1 bonus to your Evasion Bonus.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t007","name":"Iron Will","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/brain.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You gain a +1 bonus on saves made to resist fear and mind-influencing effects.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t008","name":"Power Attack","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/axe.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Before you make a melee attack, you can choose to take a -2 penalty to the attack roll.\nIf the attack hits, you add +5 to the attack's damage.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t009","name":"Cleave","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/axe.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you reduce a hostile creature to 0 Hit Points with a melee attack, you can use your reaction to make an additional melee attack against a different creature within your reach.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t010","name":"Shield Master","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/shield.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are skilled with shields.\nYou gain the weapon skill \"Shield\" with a +1 modifier.\nWhen you successfully Block an attack with a shield, you can use your reaction to shove the attacker 5 feet away.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t011","name":"Weapon Specialization","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/sword.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Choose one weapon type you are skilled with (e.g., Swords, Axes).\nYou gain a +1 bonus to damage rolls with that weapon type.\n(This talent can be taken multiple times, but must be applied to a different weapon type each time.)</p>"}}
{"_id":"t012","name":"Adrenaline Rush","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/lightning.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Once per turn, you can spend 1 WP to make one additional weapon attack as a bonus action.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t013","name":"Push Through the Pain","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/strong.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The first time you are reduced to 0 HP in a combat encounter, you are not knocked unconscious.\nInstead, you gain 1d10 temporary Hit Points. These temporary HP last until the end of the combat.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t014","name":"Evasive Footwork","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/parry.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you move, you can make a Dexterity check (DC 15).\nOn a success, opportunity attacks against you have disadvantage until the end of your turn.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t015","name":"Knowledge of Poisons","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/poison.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are knowledgeable in the art of poisons and start with a poisoner's kit.\nYou can apply poison to a weapon as a bonus action.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t016","name":"Skulker","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/eye.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You can attempt to hide even when you are only lightly obscured by dim light, fog, or other environmental effects.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t017","name":"Disarming Strike","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/sword.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can attempt to disarm the target.\nThis is a competitive roll: you make a Dexterity check against the target's Strength check.\nOn a success, the target drops one item of your choice that it's holding.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t018","name":"Master of Disguise","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/mask.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are knowledgeable in the art of disguise.\nYou have advantage on any checks made to create or maintain a disguise.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t019","name":"Lockpick","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/lock.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You are knowledgeable in the art of lockpicking and start with a lockpick kit.\nYou have advantage on any checks made to pick or disable locks.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t020","name":"Expanded Tradition","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You gain access to a new Magic Tradition.\nIt becomes a Weapon Skill for you with a starting bonus of +0.\n(This talent can be taken multiple times.)</p>"}}
{"_id":"t021","name":"Efficient Casting","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/magic-swirl.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you cast a spell that costs 1 or more WP, you can roll a d20.\nOn a result of 11 or higher, you immediately recover 1 spent Willpower Point.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t022","name":"Subtle Spell","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/whisper.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you cast a spell, you can spend 1 additional WP to cast it without any verbal or somatic components.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t023","name":"War Caster","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You have advantage on Constitution saving throws that you make to maintain your concentration on a spell when you take damage.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t024","name":"Elemental Attunement","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/fire.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Choose one element (Fire, Ice, Lightning, etc.).\nWhen you cast a spell that deals that type of damage, you add your spellcasting attribute modifier to the damage.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t025","name":"Arcane Reservoir","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your maximum Willpower Points increase by 1. (This talent can be taken multiple times.)</p>"}}
{"_id":"t026","name":"Spirit Sight","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/eye.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You learn the Spirit Sight spell, which is added to your list of known spells for the Spirit-Touched tradition.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t027","name":"Whispers of the Past","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/book.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You learn the Whispers of the Past spell, which is added to your list of known spells for the Spirit-Touched tradition.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t028","name":"Spiritual Resistance","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/aura.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You have resistance to spirit damage and gain a +1 bonus on saves against effects from ghosts, specters, and other incorporeal undead.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t029","name":"Anchor Soul","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/anchor.svg","system":{"description":"<p>When you would be forced to make a Corruption or Fatigue save from overexertion, you can choose to gain a level of exhaustion instead.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t030","name":"Voice of the Spirits","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/sound.svg","system":{"description":"<p>You learn the Voice of the Spirits spell, which is added to your list of known spells for the Spirit-Touched tradition.</p>"}}
{"_id":"t031","name":"Deeper Well","type":"talent","img":"icons/svg/d20.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your maximum Willpower Points increase by 1. (This talent can be taken multiple times.)</p>"}}
